# Definition of Done — {{PROJECT_NAME}} (Node / TypeScript)

This is a Node-stack project. The list below is the contract every change must meet before it can be called done. `/dod:checklist` reads this file and surfaces unmet items.

## Universal criteria

- [ ] All new exported functions have a JSDoc block describing parameters, return shape, and error behavior.
- [ ] No new `TODO` / `FIXME` / `XXX` / `HACK` markers in the diff.
- [ ] No function ships with a stub body (`return null`, `return undefined`, `{}`, `throw new Error("not implemented")`, empty arrow).
- [ ] No `// @ts-ignore` or `// @ts-expect-error` added in the diff (escape hatches). If unavoidable, link an issue in the comment.
- [ ] No `as any` cast added in the diff.
- [ ] No empty `catch` blocks and no `.catch(() => {})` swallowing rejections.

## Tests

- [ ] Tests added for every new code path.
- [ ] Assertions exercise real behavior — no `expect(x).toBeDefined()`, `.not.toBeNull()`, `.toBeTruthy()` as the only assertion.
- [ ] No `expect(mock).toHaveBeenCalled()` without a matching `.toHaveBeenCalledWith(...)` argument check.
- [ ] No `expect.assertions(0)`.
- [ ] No new snapshot tests with trivial output (`{}`, `[]`, single-token strings).
- [ ] No existing test deleted, skipped, `xit`-ed, or `test.skip`-ed to make the suite pass.
- [ ] `npm test` / `pnpm test` / `yarn test` passes locally.

## Build & types

- [ ] `tsc --noEmit` (or `npm run typecheck`) is clean for new TypeScript files.
- [ ] `eslint .` / `npm run lint` has no new warnings or errors.
- [ ] `package.json` `scripts.test` exists and the runner is committed to the repo (jest, vitest, mocha, or other).

## End-to-end probe

- [ ] For every new HTTP endpoint, CLI command, or user-facing function, paste the exact `curl` / CLI invocation that exercises it, with the observed response or stdout, into the PR description.
- [ ] For frontend changes, attach a screenshot or recorded interaction.

